# Q2:Write a Python script that will generate random passwords from the given list variable words, that
# you will get by utilizing the array declaration code given to you. Then, your script should assign the
# variable user_number to a value to be entered by the user. Your script should validate that the value
# of user_number must be between 3 and 7, inclusive. This value would refer to the number of words
# to be chosen randomly from the list variable words. Depending on the value of user_number, your
# code should randomly choose a number of words from the words list. Lastly, your script should
# concatenate these words into one string and reverse it to create the password and print it on the screen.
while True:
    user_number = int(input("*Enter an user number (it must be between 3 and 7 exclusive) :"))
    if user_number>=3 and user_number<=7:
        break
    else:
        print("-The user number must be between 3 and 7 exclusive!")

i=1
password = ""
while i<=user_number:
    randomNumber = random.randint(0, 999)
    password = password+words[randomNumber]
    i=i+1

print(password)

# Q3: 3. Modify your script from the 2nd question. It should run for 8 times. This means you will generate
# 8 different passwords. Create 2 empty sets ( i.e. x = set() ). Name the first set as “shorter” and the
# second set as “longer”. If user_number is smaller than 5, put newly generated password to the
# “shorter” set, else put it to the “longer” set. Lastly use union( ) method of the sets to combine these
# sets and print it on the screen.

shorter = set()
longer = set()
counter = 1

while counter<=8:
    while True:
        user_number = int(input("*Enter an user number (it must be between 3 and 7 exclusive) :"))
        if user_number >= 3 and user_number <= 7:
            break
        else:
            print("-The user number must be between 3 and 7 exclusive!")
    i = 1
    password = ""
    while i <= user_number:
        randomNumber = random.randint(0, 999)
        password = password + words[randomNumber]
        i = i + 1

    if user_number<5:
        shorter.add(password)
    else:
        longer.add(password)

    counter = counter + 1

z = shorter.union(longer)
print(z)

print()

